               <head>Demise; Brampton; 1500</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> BBAMPSTON. Indenture between <persName>
                           <forename>Adam</forename> 
                           <surname>Reyner</surname>,
                  master of the <orgName role="master" key="org_105042">hospital of St. James, Donewic</orgName></persName>, 
                  of one part, and <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Crakenell</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_105194">Brampton (Bramston)</placeName>
                        </persName> of the other, witnesseth
                  that the master and brethren and sisters of the hospital have demised to the said John two
                  pieces of land lying in <placeName key="place_105194">Brampton (Bramston)</placeName> for 30 years, at an annual rent of 2s. l0d. 
                  Dated on the feast of St. Mary Magdalen, <origDate when="1500-07-22">15 Hen. VII (22 July 1500)</origDate>. 
                  </p>
                  </msItem>
